          "description": "Atari universal modem||||||\u0026lt;br\u0026gt;\u0026lt;font color\u003d\u0026quot;red\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;strong\u0026gt;\u0026gt;\u0026nbsp;ATARI UNIVERSAL MODEM\u0026lt;/strong\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/font\u0026gt;\u0026lt;br\u0026gt;\u0026lt;blockquote\u0026gt;The SX212 modem was one of the rare Atari peripherals that could be used with all the Atari computers range, from the 400/800 series up to the Falcon. It had both the Atari I/O ports for the 8-bit systems and a standard RS-232 connector for ST\u0027s\u0026lt;br\u0026gt;\u0026lt;br\u0026gt; It was a 300/1200 baud modem compatible with the well-known Hayes \u0027AT\u0027 commands.\u0026lt;br\u0026gt; Cable and software was sold separately, depending of the computer used. \u0026lt;/blockquote\u0026gt;"
